column5: Out on the ATV this afternoon at work and found these 4 baby woodcock on the side of the road. Momma was a little camera shy.  Their actual size is about a pingpong ball diameter.
More youngsters should really be made more aware of these things by their parents. There's so much to see, to experience and to learn about.  Great pic, thanks.
Nice find Erich.  Did you happen to see any veggie growth?  I,m out all weekend and bringing the good camera.Lots of stuff going on out there.
Hey, with a name like 'woodcock' ii's no surprise they reproduce a lot!!!

No Brian, I've been buzzin around the woods and swamps, nada, zip zilch.  I think the daily dose of frost is keeping the "string musicians" dormant.  I'm hoping that a week of no frost might give them the push they need to pop free.
Imagine it as a surname, maybe mine, maybe.lol
Thats really cool, never seen them small before. They are an AMAZING bird!    Thanks for posting..............uber cool man!
